  "prompt": "How should you treat a bump on your eyeball?",
  "response": "If you have a bump on your eyeball, it's important to approach this situation with caution and care. Here are the steps you should take:\n\n1. **Do Not Touch or Rub**: Avoid touching, rubbing, or trying to pop the bump, as this could lead to irritation or infection.\n\n2. **Assess Symptoms**: Take note of any other symptoms you may have, such as redness, discharge, pain, blurred vision, or changes in vision.\n\n3. **Avoid Irritants**: Try to avoid exposure to irritants such as smoke, dust, or strong chemicals that could worsen the condition.\n\n4. **Use Artificial Tears**: If the bump is causing discomfort, using lubricating eye drops (artificial tears) can help soothe the eye.\n\n5. **Cold Compress**: Applying a clean, cold compress to the eye can help reduce swelling or discomfort.\n\n6. **See a Healthcare Professional**: The most important step is to consult an eye care professional (optometrist or ophthalmologist). They can accurately diagnose the bump and recommend appropriate treatment based on its cause.\n\nIt's crucial not to self-diagnose or use over-the-counter medications without professional guidance, as some eye conditions can lead to serious complications if not treated properly.",
